wfSmdsSwSubTable.name: wfSmdsSwSubTable
wfSmdsSwSubTable.description: The Wellfleet SMDS Switch Circuit (SNI, subscriber) Record. This record holds information on a per circuit (SSI, SNI, subscriber) basis.

wfSmdsSwSubEntry.name: wfSmdsSwSubEntry
wfSmdsSwSubEntry.description: Per Wellfleet circuit SMDS Switch configuration parameters and counters. This table contains Subscriber-Network Interface (SNI) parameters and state variables, one entry per SIP port.

wfSmdsSwSubState.name: wfSmdsSwSubState
wfSmdsSwSubState.description: SMDS Switch state variable, Up, Down Init, Not Present

wfSmdsSwSubDisableHrtbtPoll.name: wfSmdsSwSubDisableHrtbtPoll
wfSmdsSwSubDisableHrtbtPoll.description: determine use of DXI heartbeat poll

wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollAddr.name: wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollAddr
wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollAddr.description: determine if heartbeat poll messages are sent as as CPE or network (CSU/DSU) messages.

wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollInterval.name: wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollInterval
wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollInterval.description: heartbeat polling messages get sent every this many seconds - we don't want the polling interval to be less than or equal to the no-acknowledgment timer.

wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollDownCount.name: wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollDownCount
wfSmdsSwSubHrtbtPollDownCount.description: if this many consecutive heartbeat polling messages go unacknowledged, log an event declaring the line down

wfSmdsSwSubDisableNetMgmt.name: wfSmdsSwSubDisableNetMgmt
wfSmdsSwSubDisableNetMgmt.description: determine use of LMI network management

wfSmdsSwSubInterfaceType.name: wfSmdsSwSubInterfaceType
wfSmdsSwSubInterfaceType.description: defines whether this interface is a SNI or SSI.

wfSmdsSwSubInterfaceIndex.name: wfSmdsSwSubInterfaceIndex
wfSmdsSwSubInterfaceIndex.description: The index number for the SSI/SNI. Each SNI in the network has a unique id. The value of this object identifies the SIP port interface for which this entry contains management information.

wfSmdsSwSubDisableL3PduChecks.name: wfSmdsSwSubDisableL3PduChecks
wfSmdsSwSubDisableL3PduChecks.description: Enable/Disable L3_PDU verification. Default is disabled.

wfSmdsSwSubDisableUsageGeneration.name: wfSmdsSwSubDisableUsageGeneration
wfSmdsSwSubDisableUsageGeneration.description: enable/disable usage data generation. Default is disabled.

wfSmdsSwSubDisableMIR.name: wfSmdsSwSubDisableMIR
wfSmdsSwSubDisableMIR.description: enable/disable MIR enforcement, default is disabled.

wfSmdsSwSubUnassignedSAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubUnassignedSAs
wfSmdsSwSubUnassignedSAs.description: The total number of SIP Level 3 PDUs discarded by the SMDS Switch because the Source Address was not assigned to the SNI.

wfSmdsSwSubSAScreenViolations.name: wfSmdsSwSubSAScreenViolations
wfSmdsSwSubSAScreenViolations.description: The number of SIP L3_PDUs that violated the address screen based on source address screening for an SNI.

wfSmdsSwSubDAScreenViolations.name: wfSmdsSwSubDAScreenViolations
wfSmdsSwSubDAScreenViolations.description: The total number of SIP Level 3 PDUs that violated the Destination Address Screening using either an Individual Address Screen or a Group Address Screen for the SNI.

wfSmdsSwSubNumPDUExceededMIR.name: wfSmdsSwSubNumPDUExceededMIR
wfSmdsSwSubNumPDUExceededMIR.description: The total number of SIP L3_PDUs that exceeded the MIR on this interface.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3ReceivedIAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3ReceivedIAs
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3ReceivedIAs.description: The total number of individually addressed SIP Level 3 PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE. The total includes only unerrored L3PDUs.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3ReceivedGAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3ReceivedGAs
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3ReceivedGAs.description: The total number of group addressed SIP Level 3 PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE. The total includes only unerrored L3PDUs.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3UnrecIAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3UnrecIAs
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3UnrecIAs.description: The number of SIP Level 3 PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE that have an unknown, valid, individual SMDS Destination Address.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3UnrecGAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3UnrecGAs
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3UnrecGAs.description: The number of SIP Level 3 PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE that have an unknown, valid, group SMDS Destination Address.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3SentIAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3SentIAs
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3SentIAs.description: The number of individually addressed SIP Level 3 PDUs that have been sent by this SMDS Switch to the CPE.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3SentGAs.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3SentGAs
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3SentGAs.description: The number of group addressed SIP L3PDUs that have been sent by this SMDS Switch to the CPE.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3Errors.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3Errors
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3Errors.description: The total number of SIP Level 3 PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE that were discovered to have protocol errors.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3InvAddrTypes.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3InvAddrTypes
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3InvAddrTypes.description: The total number of SIP Level 3 PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE that had a value in the Source or Destination Address type subfield other than group or individual. Or if the Source Address type subfield value indicates a group address.

wfSmdsSwSubSipL3VersionSupport.name: wfSmdsSwSubSipL3VersionSupport
wfSmdsSwSubSipL3VersionSupport.description: A value which indicates the version(s) of SIP that this SNI supports. The value is a sum. This sum initially takes the value zero. For each version, V, that this interface supports, 2 raised to (V - 1) is added to the sum. For example, a port supporting versions 1 and 2 would have a value of (2^(1-1)+2^(2-1))=3. The SipL3VersionSupport is effectively a bit mask with Version 1 equal to the least significant bit (LSB).

wfSmdsSwSubSAScrnViolationOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubSAScrnViolationOccur
wfSmdsSwSubSAScrnViolationOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded as a result of a Source Address violation.

wfSmdsSwSubDAScrnViolationOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubDAScrnViolationOccur
wfSmdsSwSubDAScrnViolationOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded as a result of a Destination Address violation.

wfSmdsSwSubUnassignedSAOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubUnassignedSAOccur
wfSmdsSwSubUnassignedSAOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded as a result of a unassigned Source Address.

wfSmdsSwSubSAErrorOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubSAErrorOccur
wfSmdsSwSubSAErrorOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of a Source Address Field Format error.

wfSmdsSwSubDAErrorOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubDAErrorOccur
wfSmdsSwSubDAErrorOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of a Destination Address Field Format error.

wfSmdsSwSubInvalidBASizeOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubInvalidBASizeOccur
wfSmdsSwSubInvalidBASizeOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of an invalid BASize field value.

wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHELenOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHELenOccur
wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHELenOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of an invalid Header Extension Length Field value.

wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHEVerOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHEVerOccur
wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHEVerOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of an invalid Header Extension Version element.

wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHECarOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHECarOccur
wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHECarOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of an invalid Header Extension Carrier element.

wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHEPadOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHEPadOccur
wfSmdsSwSubInvalidHEPadOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of an invalid Header Extension Pad element.

wfSmdsSwSubBEtagOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubBEtagOccur
wfSmdsSwSubBEtagOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of a Beginning-End Tag mismatch.

wfSmdsSwSubBAsizeNELenOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubBAsizeNELenOccur
wfSmdsSwSubBAsizeNELenOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because the BAsize and Length fields are not equal.

wfSmdsSwSubIncorrectLenOccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubIncorrectLenOccur
wfSmdsSwSubIncorrectLenOccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because of an incorrect length.

wfSmdsSwSubExceededMIROccur.name: wfSmdsSwSubExceededMIROccur
wfSmdsSwSubExceededMIROccur.description: A string containing the SMDS Source Address, Destination Address, and Event time of the most recent occurance of an L3_PDU discarded because it exceeded the MIR.

wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtDisable.name: wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtDisable
wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtDisable.description: In-Band Management enable/disable parameter. This attribute indicates whether the local WSNI (only) is enabled to run IP in Host mode, for in-band management purposes, in additional to being a switch interface. The default is disabled

wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtLocalAddr.name: wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtLocalAddr
wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtLocalAddr.description: Special SMDS E.164 Individual address that identifies this local circuit. This attribute is only used when the wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtDisable attribute is set to ENABLED

wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtReceivedPDUs.name: wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtReceivedPDUs
wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtReceivedPDUs.description: The total number of individually addressed In-Band Management PDUs received by the SMDS Switch from the CPE. The total includes only unerrored PDUs.

wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtSentPDUs.name: wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtSentPDUs
wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtSentPDUs.description: The number of individually addressed In-Band Management PDUs that have been sent by this SMDS Switch to the CPE.

wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtMaxLenErrors.name: wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtMaxLenErrors
wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtMaxLenErrors.description: The number of In-Band Management PDUs that have exceeded the MTU size configured for the line

wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtEncapsErrors.name: wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtEncapsErrors
wfSmdsSwSubInBandMgmtEncapsErrors.description: The number of In-Band Management PDUs that have invalid encapsulation schemes

wfSmdsSwSubGAPartialResolve.name: wfSmdsSwSubGAPartialResolve
wfSmdsSwSubGAPartialResolve.description: The number of times group addressed L3_PDU's could not be resolved due to congestion.

wfSmdsSwSubDANotOnSni.name: wfSmdsSwSubDANotOnSni
wfSmdsSwSubDANotOnSni.description: The number of times a L3_PDU was discarded at the egress because the destination address was not assigned to the SNI.

wfSmdsSwEndpTable.name: wfSmdsSwEndpTable
wfSmdsSwEndpTable.description: The Parameters for the Endpoint table. An Endpoint is defined as an IP address, SMDS E.164 address pair. Endpoint ranges should never overlap.

wfSmdsSwEndpEntry.name: wfSmdsSwEndpEntry
wfSmdsSwEndpEntry.description: The parameters for a particular Endpoint.

wfSmdsSwEndpDelete.name: wfSmdsSwEndpDelete
wfSmdsSwEndpDelete.description: Indication to delete this endpoint entry.

wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrHigh.name: wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrHigh
wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrHigh.description: The High end of the E.164 address range for this endpoint information.

wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrDelta.name: wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrDelta
wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrDelta.description: The difference between wfSmdsSwEndpE164AddrHigh to the beginning of the endpoint information.

wfSmdsSwEndpInterfaceIndex.name: wfSmdsSwEndpInterfaceIndex
wfSmdsSwEndpInterfaceIndex.description: This number indicates which SNI the endpoint information refers to.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceTable.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceTable
wfSmdsSwInterfaceTable.description: This is the Interface Table. This table also holds the Maximum Information Rate (MIR) information.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceEntry.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceEntry
wfSmdsSwInterfaceEntry.description: This table defines the IP addresses and what interfaces they are associated with.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceDelete.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceDelete
wfSmdsSwInterfaceDelete.description: Indication to delete this interface entry.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceType.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceType
wfSmdsSwInterfaceType.description: This number determines whether the interface information refers to an SNI, SSI, or ICI.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceIndex.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceIndex
wfSmdsSwInterfaceIndex.description: This number indicates which SNI, SSI, or ICI the interface information refers to.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceIpAddr.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceIpAddr
wfSmdsSwInterfaceIpAddr.description: IP Address associated with the interface.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceMIR.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceMIR
wfSmdsSwInterfaceMIR.description: This number represents the MIR in octets per second.

wfSmdsSwInterfaceCurrentRate.name: wfSmdsSwInterfaceCurrentRate
wfSmdsSwInterfaceCurrentRate.description: This number indicates the current rate of traffic flow to the interface. The software updates this counter. When this attribute exceeds wfSmdsSwInterfaceMIR traffic to the interface is dropped. Periodically the sofware resets this counter to zero.

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnTable.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnTable
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnTable.description: This list identifies the associated SNI addresses per individualand group address screen. Different addresses on an SNI may be associated with different individual and group address screens (one individual address screen per associated address on an SNI, and one group address screen per associated address on an SNI ).

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnEntry.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnEntry
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnEntry.description: An SNI index, group and individual screening list index, and the associated addresses for the SNI for the address screens.

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnDelete.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnDelete
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnDelete.description: Indication to delete this associated screen entry.

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnSniIndex.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnSniIndex
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnSniIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the SIP Port interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex, defined in RFC1213, for the same interface.

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnAddrInd.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnAddrInd
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnAddrInd.description: The value of this object identifies one of the SMDS addresses for the SNI, identified by the wfSmdsSwAssocScrnSniIndex that belongs to this individual (or group) address screen (wfSmdsSwAssocScrnAddrInd). This list will contain both individual and group addresses, because this list is used for both Destination Address Screening and Source Address Screening; the destination address in the L3_PDU that is undergoing Source Address Screening may be either a group or individual address that is assigned to that SNI. One screen will have a maximum of 64 associated addresses; up to a maximum of 16 individual addresses identifying an SNI and up to a maximum of 48 group addresses identifying an SNI.

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnIndivIndex.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnIndivIndex
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnIndivIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the individual address screening list. There is at least one individual address screen and at most s individual address screens per SNI. The initial value of s is defined to be 4. In the future more screening lists per SNI may be allowed. The values of this object correspond to the values of wfSmdsSwIAScrnIndex in the wfSmdsSwIAScrnTable.

wfSmdsSwAssocScrnGrpIndex.name: wfSmdsSwAssocScrnGrpIndex
wfSmdsSwAssocScrnGrpIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the group address screening list. There is at least one group address screen and at most s group address screens per SNI. The initial value of s is defined to be 4. In the future more screening lists per SNI may be allowed. The values of this object correspond to the values of wfSmdsSwGAScrnIndex in the wfSmdsSwGAScrnTable. This field applies only to individual addresses on the SNI because it applies only to destination address screening of group addresses.

wfSmdsSwIAScrnTable.name: wfSmdsSwIAScrnTable
wfSmdsSwIAScrnTable.description: This list identifies the individual addresses that will be screened per individual address screen table. The are up to s (s is equal to 4) individual address screens per SNI and at least one individual address screen per SNI. The Individual Address Screens and the Group Address Screens together consist of up to n addresses. The initial value of n is defined as 128. In the future a value of n up to 2048 may be supported. The Individual Address Screen is used to perform Destination Address Screening for individually addressed data units and Source Address Screening for all data units. The Group Address Screen is used to perform Destination Address Screening for group addressed data units.

wfSmdsSwIAScrnEntry.name: wfSmdsSwIAScrnEntry
wfSmdsSwIAScrnEntry.description: An SNI index, a screening list index, the individual addresses to be screened for the individual address screen, and whether the screened address is valid or invalid.

wfSmdsSwIAScrnDelete.name: wfSmdsSwIAScrnDelete
wfSmdsSwIAScrnDelete.description: Indication to delete this IA screen entry.

wfSmdsSwIAScrnSniIndex.name: wfSmdsSwIAScrnSniIndex
wfSmdsSwIAScrnSniIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the SIP Port interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex, defined in RFC1213, for the same interface.

wfSmdsSwIAScrnIndex.name: wfSmdsSwIAScrnIndex
wfSmdsSwIAScrnIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the individual address screening list. There are at least one individual address screen and at most s individual address screens per SNI. The initial value of s is defined to be 4. In the future more screening lists per SNI may be allowed. The values of this object correspond to the values of wfSmdsSwScrnIndex in the wfSmdsSwScrnTable.

wfSmdsSwIAScrnAddr.name: wfSmdsSwIAScrnAddr
wfSmdsSwIAScrnAddr.description: The value of this object identifies one of the individual addresses to be screened for source and destination address screening for the SNI identified by the wfSmdsSwIAScrnSniIndex and for the particular individual address screen (wfSmdsSwIAScrnIndex).

wfSmdsSwGAScrnTable.name: wfSmdsSwGAScrnTable
wfSmdsSwGAScrnTable.description: This list identifies the group addresses that will be screened per group address screen table. The are up to s (s is equal to 4) group address screens per SNI and at least one group address screen per SNI. The Individual Address Screen and the Group Address Screen together consist of up to n addresses. The initial value of n is defined as 128. In the future a value of n up to 2048 may be supported. The Individual Address Screen is used to perform Destination Address Screening for individually addressed data units and Source Address Screening for all data units. The Group Address Screen is used to perform Destination Address Screening for group addressed data units.

wfSmdsSwGAScrnEntry.name: wfSmdsSwGAScrnEntry
wfSmdsSwGAScrnEntry.description: An SNI index, a screening list index, the group addresses to be screened for the group address screen, and whether the screened address is valid or invalid.

wfSmdsSwGAScrnDelete.name: wfSmdsSwGAScrnDelete
wfSmdsSwGAScrnDelete.description: Indication to delete this GA screen entry.

wfSmdsSwGAScrnSniIndex.name: wfSmdsSwGAScrnSniIndex
wfSmdsSwGAScrnSniIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the SIP Port interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex, defined in RFC1213, for the same interface.

wfSmdsSwGAScrnIndex.name: wfSmdsSwGAScrnIndex
wfSmdsSwGAScrnIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the group address screening list. There is at least one group address screen and at most s group address screens per SNI. The initial value of s is defined to be 4. In the future more screening lists per SNI may be allowed. The values of this object correspond to the values of wfSmdsSwScrnIndex in the wfSmdsSwSmdsScrnTable.

wfSmdsSwGAScrnAddr.name: wfSmdsSwGAScrnAddr
wfSmdsSwGAScrnAddr.description: The value of this object identifies one of the group addresses to be screened for destination address screening for the SNI identified by the wfSmdsSwGAScrnSniIndex and for the particular group address screen (wfSmdsSwGAScrnIndex).

wfSmdsSwGATable.name: wfSmdsSwGATable
wfSmdsSwGATable.description: A table of all group addresses in the network and the associated individual addresses identified by each group address. A group address identifies up to m individual addresses. An SMDS SS supports up to n group addresses. A group address can be identified by up to p individual addresses. A particular SNI is identified by up to 48 group addresses. The initial values of m, n, and p are defined as 128, 1024, and 32, respectively. In the future values of m and n of 2048 and 8192, respectively, may be supported.

wfSmdsSwGAEntry.name: wfSmdsSwGAEntry
wfSmdsSwGAEntry.description: A Group Address and an address in that group and whether that association is valid or invalid.

wfSmdsSwGADelete.name: wfSmdsSwGADelete
wfSmdsSwGADelete.description: Indication to delete this group address entry.

wfSmdsSwGASSI.name: wfSmdsSwGASSI
wfSmdsSwGASSI.description: The SSI associated with this Group Address. An SSI of 0 is used to indicate that all interfaces can use the group address. An SSI other than 0 indicates that only the SSI, or an SNI associated with the SSI should use the group.

wfSmdsSwGAGroupMember.name: wfSmdsSwGAGroupMember
wfSmdsSwGAGroupMember.description: An individual SMDS address that belongs to this Group Address.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageTable.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageTable
wfSmdsSwCurUsageTable.description: This table contains the Current Usage Data. This is the interface between Billing and Switching. The Switch gates create these records. The Billing gates collect them to create billing data.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageEntry.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageEntry
wfSmdsSwCurUsageEntry.description: The usage data for the current usage period indexed by destination,source address.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageDelete.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageDelete
wfSmdsSwCurUsageDelete.description: Indication to delete this current usage entry.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageSni.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageSni
wfSmdsSwCurUsageSni.description: The SNI number of the interface generating the usage information

wfSmdsSwCurUsageDestAddr.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageDestAddr
wfSmdsSwCurUsageDestAddr.description: The destination address of a SMDS group or individual E.164 address.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageSrcAddr.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageSrcAddr
wfSmdsSwCurUsageSrcAddr.description: The source address of a SMDS individual E.164 address.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageGrpIndAddr.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageGrpIndAddr
wfSmdsSwCurUsageGrpIndAddr.description: When the destination address of an L3_PDU is a group address, this attribute is set to one of the E.164 individual addresses that is in the group address and on the destination SNI.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu
wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu.description: This number represents the number of billable L3_PDUs counted by the circuit during the most recent collection interval.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctet.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctet
wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctet.description: This number represents the number of billable octets counted by the circuit during the most recent collection interval.

wfSmdsSwCurUsageToBeDeleted.name: wfSmdsSwCurUsageToBeDeleted
wfSmdsSwCurUsageToBeDeleted.description: Indication to billing to delete this current usage entry.

wfSmdsSwUsageVolume.name: wfSmdsSwUsageVolume
wfSmdsSwUsageVolume.description: Indicates the file system volume number to which the billing usage data files will be written. The volume number corresponds to the slot number on which the volume resides. Note: Value 0 has the special meaning that no 'Store' and 'Flush' operations will take place. This translates to no Billing data will be written to the local file system. 'Update' operations will still be performed on each local slot. Full Billing statistics will still be available in the wfSmdsSwUsageTable MIB.

wfSmdsSwUsageVolumeBackup.name: wfSmdsSwUsageVolumeBackup
wfSmdsSwUsageVolumeBackup.description: Indicates the backup volume if wfSmdsSwUsageVolume becomes inoperative. Note: This feature is not implemented in this release.

wfSmdsSwUsageDirectory.name: wfSmdsSwUsageDirectory
wfSmdsSwUsageDirectory.description: The name of the directory where the billing usage data files are stored.

wfSmdsSwUsageFilePrefix.name: wfSmdsSwUsageFilePrefix
wfSmdsSwUsageFilePrefix.description: The base name of billing usage data files.

wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval.description: This number determines the timer interval (number of seconds) unit for the Billing process to perform its various timer driven tasks. i.e. updating billing usage data, writing billing usage data to file system and file system management activities.

wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to collect and update billing usage data in the wfSmdsSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to write billing usage data on to the file system from the wfSmdsSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval.description: This number specifies the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to write billing usage data on to the file system from the wfSmdsSwUsage MIB followed by zeroing the wfSmdsSwUsage MIB. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multiple of wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval.description: This is the interval (number of minutes) for the Billing process to check and delete old billing usage data files. Note: When converted to seconds, this must be a multilple of wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval.

wfSmdsSwUsageLocalTimeZone.name: wfSmdsSwUsageLocalTimeZone
wfSmdsSwUsageLocalTimeZone.description: Indicates local time zone of the switch

wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateTimeStamp.name: wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateTimeStamp
wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageStoreTimeStamp.name: wfSmdsSwUsageStoreTimeStamp
wfSmdsSwUsageStoreTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageFlushTimeStamp.name: wfSmdsSwUsageFlushTimeStamp
wfSmdsSwUsageFlushTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupTimeStamp.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupTimeStamp
wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of last wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval timer expiration or the starting time of the current wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval. This value is number of seconds since midnight Jan. 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateData.name: wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateData
wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating of the billing usage data. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfSmdsSwUsageStoreData.name: wfSmdsSwUsageStoreData
wfSmdsSwUsageStoreData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating and writing of the billing usage data. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfSmdsSwUsageFlushData.name: wfSmdsSwUsageFlushData
wfSmdsSwUsageFlushData.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate updating and writing of the billing usage data and followed by zeroing the wfSmdsSwBillingUsage MIB. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfSmdsSwUsageFileCleanup.name: wfSmdsSwUsageFileCleanup
wfSmdsSwUsageFileCleanup.description: Setting this attribute to a non-zero value will cause an immediate checking and deleting old billing usage data files. Once activated, this attribute should be reset to zero to allow subsequent activations.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurVolume.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurVolume
wfSmdsSwUsageCurVolume.description: current file system volume number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageVolume except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageVolume to an invalid number.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurVolumeBackup.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurVolumeBackup
wfSmdsSwUsageCurVolumeBackup.description: curent backup file system volume number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageVolumeBackUp except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageVolume to an invalid number. Note: This feature is not implemented in this release.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurDirectory.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurDirectory
wfSmdsSwUsageCurDirectory.description: current directory name used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageDirectory except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageDirectory to an invalid name.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurFilePrefix.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurFilePrefix
wfSmdsSwUsageCurFilePrefix.description: current base file name used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageFilePrefix except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageFilePrefix to an invalid name.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurTimerInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurTimerInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageCurTimerInterval.description: current timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageTimerInterval to an invalid value.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurUpdateInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurUpdateInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageCurUpdateInterval.description: current update interval number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageUpdateInterval to an invalid value.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurStoreInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurStoreInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageCurStoreInterval.description: current store timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageStoreInterval to an invalid value.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurFlushInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurFlushInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageCurFlushInterval.description: current flush timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageFlushInterval to an invalid value.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurCleanupInterval.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurCleanupInterval
wfSmdsSwUsageCurCleanupInterval.description: current file cleanup timer interval number used. This number is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageCleanupInterval to an invalid value.

wfSmdsSwUsageDebug.name: wfSmdsSwUsageDebug
wfSmdsSwUsageDebug.description: Enable/Disable printing of debug edl (trap) messages. NOTE: Do not enable this attribute in operational enviornment as it will likely flood the logging facility. This attribute is reserved for specialized debugging in a controlled lab enviornment.

wfSmdsSwUsageCurDebug.name: wfSmdsSwUsageCurDebug
wfSmdsSwUsageCurDebug.description: current debug value used. This value is the same as wfSmdsSwUsageDebug except when the user sets wfSmdsSwUsageDeubg to an invalid value.

wfSmdsSwUsageSwitchId.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSwitchId
wfSmdsSwUsageSwitchId.description: switch id used in the billing usage data file.

wfSmdsSwUsageDelete.name: wfSmdsSwUsageDelete
wfSmdsSwUsageDelete.description: Indicates status of this entry. SMDS_SW_USAGE_CREATED is the normal case. SMDS_SW_USAGE_DELETED means this billing instance will be deleted at the end of the next wfSmdsSwUsageFlush period after this billing record is written out to the file system.

wfSmdsSwUsageSni.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSni
wfSmdsSwUsageSni.description: The circuit number of the interface generating the usage information

wfSmdsSwUsageDestAddr.name: wfSmdsSwUsageDestAddr
wfSmdsSwUsageDestAddr.description: Instance identifier; the destination address of an L3_PDU. The SMDS Switch collects usage data based on the destination/source address pair.

wfSmdsSwUsageSrcAddr.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSrcAddr
wfSmdsSwUsageSrcAddr.description: Instance identifier; the source address of an L3_PDU. The SMDS Switch collects usage data based on the destination/source address pair.

wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStampHigh.name: wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStampHigh
wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStampHigh.description: Time stamp of the starting time (the high 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStampLow.name: wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStampLow
wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStampLow.description: Time stamp of the starting time (the low 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStampHigh.name: wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStampHigh
wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStampHigh.description: Time stamp of the ending time (the high 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStampLow.name: wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStampLow
wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStampLow.description: Time stamp of the ending time (the low 32 bits) of last billing usage interval. This value is the number of 1/100th seconds since midnight Jan 1, 1976 (GMT).

wfSmdsSwUsageSentL3PduHigh.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSentL3PduHigh
wfSmdsSwUsageSentL3PduHigh.description: Number (the high 32 bits) of L3_PDUs sent to the CPE between wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfSmdsSwUsageSentL3PduLow.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSentL3PduLow
wfSmdsSwUsageSentL3PduLow.description: Number (the low 32 bits) of L3_PDUs sent to the CPE between wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfSmdsSwUsageSentOctetHigh.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSentOctetHigh
wfSmdsSwUsageSentOctetHigh.description: Number (the high 32 bits) of octets sent to the CPE between wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfSmdsSwUsageSentOctetLow.name: wfSmdsSwUsageSentOctetLow
wfSmdsSwUsageSentOctetLow.description: Number (the low 32 bits) of octets sent to the CPE between wfSmdsSwUsageStartTimeStamp and wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfSmdsSwUsageLastL3PduHigh.name: wfSmdsSwUsageLastL3PduHigh
wfSmdsSwUsageLastL3PduHigh.description: The (high 32 bits) value of wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu value at wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp. Note: Since wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu is a 32-bit COUNTER, this is really a counter keeping track of number of times wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu has wrapped around.

wfSmdsSwUsageLastL3PduLow.name: wfSmdsSwUsageLastL3PduLow
wfSmdsSwUsageLastL3PduLow.description: The (low 32 bits) value of wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumL3Pdu value at wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfSmdsSwUsageLastOctetHigh.name: wfSmdsSwUsageLastOctetHigh
wfSmdsSwUsageLastOctetHigh.description: The (high 32 bits) value of wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctets value at wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp. Note: Since wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctets is a 32-bit COUNTER, this is really a counter keeping track of number of times wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctets has wrapped around.

wfSmdsSwUsageLastOctetLow.name: wfSmdsSwUsageLastOctetLow
wfSmdsSwUsageLastOctetLow.description: The (low 32 bits) value of wfSmdsSwCurUsageNumOctets value at wfSmdsSwUsageEndTimeStamp.

wfSmdsSwUsageGrpIndAddr.name: wfSmdsSwUsageGrpIndAddr
wfSmdsSwUsageGrpIndAddr.description: When the destination address of an L3_PDU is a group address, this attribute is set to one of the E.164 individual addresses that is in the group address and on the destination SNI.

wfSmdsSwSsiSniTable.name: wfSmdsSwSsiSniTable
wfSmdsSwSsiSniTable.description: The Parameters for the SSI/SNI Object. This object associates SNI's with SSI's for Bellcore TR-TSV-001239 compliance.

wfSmdsSwSsiSniEntry.name: wfSmdsSwSsiSniEntry
wfSmdsSwSsiSniEntry.description: The parameters for a particular SSI/SNI.

wfSmdsSwSsiSniDelete.name: wfSmdsSwSsiSniDelete
wfSmdsSwSsiSniDelete.description: Indication to delete this SSI/SNI entry.
